<http://www.agriholland.nl/dossiers/qkoorts/#hoeveel>


How many dairy sheep and dairy goats are there in the Netherlands?
-----------------------------------------------------------------
According to the 2009 data of the Dutch agricultural census, there
are 230 000 dairy goats in the Netherlands, distributed among 600
farms. About half of them keep more than 100 goats. Most of the goat
holdings are situated in the provinces Gelderland and Noord Brabant.
The number of dairy sheep is estimated to be about 10 000. There are
about 40 commercially operational, milk producing sheep farms.

--
Communicated by:
A Dutch subscriber, in response to ProMED-mail's queries in posting
20100103.0028.

